Alcoa Corporation (NYSE:AA) Stock Closed 10.5% Above Its 50 Day Moving Average - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Alcoa Corporation (NYSE:AA) Stock Closed 10.5% Above Its 50 Day Moving Average
July 24, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Company shares last traded at $36.62 slightly over the 50 day moving average of $33.13 and which is marginally higher than the 200 day moving average of $33.85.  The 50 day moving average was up by +10.55% whereas the 200 day average was up by +8.18%.  Alcoa Corporation shares had a trading volume of 2,449K by the end of trading on Friday.  Overall, volume was down 90.10% under the stocks normal daily volume. 
 Here are a few other firms who have also updated their positions.   As of quarter end Carmignac Gestion had acquired 10,001 shares growing its holdings by 2.7%. The value of the investment in Alcoa Corporation went from $10,390,000 to $13,072,000 increasing 25.8% since the last quarter. As of the end of the quarter Meeder Asset Management Inc had sold  a total of 13,376 shares trimming its stake by 93.5%. The value of the investment in (AA) decreased from $133,000 to $32,000 a change of 75.9% quarter to quarter.
 As of the end of the quarter Norges Bank had disposed of 6,346,747 shares trimming its position 23.0%. The value in dollars went from $266,889,000 to $203,878,000 a change of $63,011,000 quarter over quarter. Meag Munich Ergo Kapitalanlagegesellschaft Mbh downsized its position by selling 1,746,414 shares a decrease of 99.5%. Meag Munich Ergo Kapitalanlagegesellschaft Mbh now controls 8,000 shares worth $267,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 98.5%.





  On May 22, 2017 Clarksons Platou started coverage giving it an initial rating of “Outperform”. Argus Research added the stock to its research portfolio with a rating of “Buy”.
 Equity analyst Deutsche Bank started covering AA by announcing an initial rating of “Sell”. On November 7 analysts at Cowen & Co. began coverage of the stock setting a rating of “Overweight”.
 Equity analyst Bank of America starting coverage on AA with an initial rating of “Sell”. On November 2 analysts at Goldman Sachs released its first research report on the stock setting a rating of “Neutral”.
 In the market the company is trading down from yesterday’s close of $36.72.  The company’s P/E ratio is 41.33 and the market cap of the company is 6.75B.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $0.19 and is projected to be $2.80 for the current year with 184,257,000 shares outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is expected be $0.89 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $2.62. 
 Alcoa Corporation produces and sells bauxite, alumina, and aluminum products. It operates through six segments, Bauxite, Alumina, Aluminum, Cast Products, Energy, and Rolled Products. The company also offers aluminum cast products; and aluminum sheets for the production of cans for beverage, food, and pet food. In addition, it engages in the generation and sale of renewable energy, as well as provision of ancillary services. The company was formerly known as Alcoa Upstream Corporation and changed its name to Alcoa Corporation in October 2016. Alcoa Corporation is based in New York, New York..






