Alcoa Corporation (NYSE:AA) Trading Volume Significantly Lower 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsAlcoa Corporation (NYSE:AA) Trading Volume Significantly Lower
July 21, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



4,746K shares changed hands on Friday.  Overall, volume was down 80.81% under the stocks normal daily volume. 
 The following firms have also recently changed their position in AA.   Carmignac Gestion expanded its holdings by buying 10,001 shares an increase of 2.7% from 12/31/2016 to 03/31/2017. Carmignac Gestion controls 380,000 shares with a value of $13,072,000. The total value of its holdings increased 25.8%. As of the end of the quarter Meeder Asset Management Inc had sold 13,376 shares trimming its stake by 93.5%. The value of the company’s investment in Alcoa Corporation decreased from $133,000 to $32,000 a change of 75.9% for the reporting period.
 As of quarter end Norges Bank had disposed of  a total of 6,346,747 shares trimming its position 23.0%. The value of the investment in Alcoa Corporation went from $266,889,000 to $203,878,000 decreasing 23.6% quarter over quarter. As of the end of the quarter Meag Munich Ergo Kapitalanlagegesellschaft Mbh had sold 1,746,414 shares trimming its holdings by 99.5%. The value of the total investment in Alcoa Corporation decreased from $17,487,000 to $267,000 a change of $17,220,000 quarter to quarter.
  Equity analyst Clarksons Platou began coverage with a rating of “Outperform”. Argus Research starting coverage on AA setting a rating of “Buy”.        Advertisement






 On December 1, 2016 Deutsche Bank initiated coverage on AA with an initial rating of “Sell”. On November 7 analysts at Cowen & Co. began coverage of AA by announcing an initial rating of “Overweight”.
 Equity analyst Bank of America initiated coverage giving it an initial rating of “Sell”. On November 2 analysts at Goldman Sachs started covering AA by announcing an initial rating of “Neutral”.
 The company is trading up by 0.60% since yesterday’s close of $36.5.  The stock last traded at $36.72 just a bit higher than the 50 day moving average of $33.13 and which is marginally higher than the 200 day moving average of $33.85.  The 50 day moving average was up by +10.85% whereas the 200 day moving average was up $2.87 or +8.47%. 
 The P/E ratio is currently 197.42 and the market value is 6.77B.  In the latest earnings report the EPS was $0.19 and is expected to be $2.83 for the current year with 184,240,000 shares now outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted to be $0.89 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $2.60. 
 Alcoa Corporation produces and sells bauxite, alumina, and aluminum products. It operates through six segments, Bauxite, Alumina, Aluminum, Cast Products, Energy, and Rolled Products. The company also offers aluminum cast products; and aluminum sheets for the production of cans for beverage, food, and pet food. In addition, it engages in the generation and sale of renewable energy, as well as provision of ancillary services. The company was formerly known as Alcoa Upstream Corporation and changed its name to Alcoa Corporation in October 2016. Alcoa Corporation is based in New York, New York..
